  "referred_to_by": [
    {
      "type": "LinguisticObject",
      "content": "This is an 18th-century inclined plane demonstration apparatus (*hellend vlak*), built after the design of Willem Jacob 's Gravesande (1688–1742), the pioneering Leiden professor who introduced experimental demonstration-based physics teaching to continental Europe. The instrument was made by the Amsterdam instrument-making partnership of J. Kampman and Adam Steitz, active in the third quarter of the 18th century. It belongs to the tradition of Newtonian physics demonstration apparatus that 's Gravesande codified in his landmark textbook *Physices Elementa Mathematica* (1720).",
